            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-10-16T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-10-16T22:00:00-05:00" n="747" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d747">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">761.93/10–1745: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Robertson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-10-17T10:00:00+07:00">October 17, 1945—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 11:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1813. Under date October 15 Consul Ward at Tihwa reports the arrival at Tihwa on
                    October 12 of three delegations from Ining; these delegations (two Uighurs and
                    one Kazak) were formally introduced by the Soviet Consul General to the special
                    commissioner of the Foreign Office on October 13. (Embassy’s 1788, October 12 to
                    Department, <pb facs="1027" n="1017" xml:id="pg_1017"/> repeated to Moscow.)
                    Ward states that, accompanied by Liang Han-chao, General Chang Chih-chung
                    arrived at Tihwa on October 14 and discussions were expected to begin on morning
                    of October 15. (Sent to Department, repeated to Moscow.) Ward adds that General
                    Chu Shao-liang states that all is quiet except at Tacheng where fighting
                    continues.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robertson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
